	<Title>
		Recipe: Apple salad with figs and almonds
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Apple salad with figs and almonds &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		6
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Figs are a sweet fruit with soft flesh and tiny edible seeds. They are a good source of iron, calcium and phosphorus. You can eat figs raw, with or without their peel, or use them in baked goods. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a small bowl, combine apples, figs and celery. Add yogurt and mix thoroughly. Top with almonds and grated carrots. Serve. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 large red apples, cored and diced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;6 dried figs, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 ribs of celery, diced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup fat-free lemon yogurt&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 tablespoons slivered almonds&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 carrots, peeled and grated &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
